                                @{b}@{u}CIRCLESOFT@{uu}@{ub}


CircleSoft is a sub-group of Circle. And Circle is... yes.

CircleSoft's aim is to develop painfully great software. Nothing else.

Our motto is not. No. Mottos are irrelevant, we just try to make good
software. Publishing software? It happens, albeit not as often as we make a
great product. We won't hesitate to send you partially finished programs
though, just for the pleasure of seeing your computer go down.

CircleSoft is essentially all of Circle, which you may or may not find
information about in the address:

    http://www.abo.fi/~rsmeds/circle/

However, there are two names you should know by heart. Learn to self-impose
euphoria when you hear these names, learn to enjoy the hedonistic pleasure
that immerses your body when you hear these names: @{i}Dag @{ui}and @{i}Manne.@{ui}

What's more? What do you want to hear? That we will continue our support of
the Amiga? We will. That we are quality aware? We dare say so. That we will
revolutionize the pleasure of computing? We already have...

Now... what you should do is to download all of our software from:

    http://www.abo.fi/~mamannev/circlesoft/

See @{"Contacts" link CONTACT} for more info on how to contact us.

@endnode
@node PRODUCTS "Tickle92.guide/Other Products"
@prev CIRCLESOFT
@next CREDITS

                      @{b}@{u}OTHER PRODUCTS FROM CIRCLESOFT@{uu}@{ub}


Most of these can be found on our webpage at:

    http://www.abo.fi/~mamannev/circlesoft/

However, there are programs that haven't been put up there, but mail
@{i}mamannev@abo.fi@{ui} and ask for any program on the list and we will send it to
you.

@{b}LotsaBlankers@{ub} - The best collection of blankers for GarshneBlankers,
    featuring highlights such as; LotsaDistortion, that distorts the
    screen, LotsaLego, that builds random constructions of Lego, and
    LotsaPlasma, that generates lovely plasmas.

@{b}Misc@{ub} - A note keeping and logging program. Especially great for developers,
    who want to keep track of their software development. But great also to
    anyone, who wants to note things down without using PostIt(TM) notes.

@{b}Maggot@{ub} - A worm game with free movement, and many features. It's
    customizable, and it's the best timekiller. Naturally there is a good
    highscorelist.

@{b}Ripley@{ub} - An interactive water simulation program. Allows the user to create
    different kinds of waves on a surface of water. Feature highlights are
    bumpmapping, variable screensize, rain simulation, and picture
    distortion.

@{b}Tickle@{ub} - A computer to calculator link program for Texas Instruments's
    TI-85 and TI-92.

@{b}WBCLI@{ub} - A handy one-line CLI that can be used as an execute-command
    replacement.

@{b}Blobz@{ub} - A lovely realtime 2D blobz program. You can create slimy structures
    of your favourite type.

@{b}EggShell@{ub} - An all new shell replacement. Among other things, it features
    automatic viewing/playing of images, sound files, textfiles,
    animations, etc on their execution. Also it features default arguments
    for programs, a better prompt, and many other things that make your
    command line life easier.

@{b}Loves@{ub} - A cute program which finds out who loves who, and how much these
    people love each other.

@{b}3DTanxX@{ub} - An artillery duel type game in 3D.

@{b}Bullet@{ub} - A useful program that allows you to blast holes in the desktop.

@{b}LED@{ub} - A small, compact text editor, that features all basic features in an
    editor.

@{b}Morse-Daemon@{ub} - A program that allows you to send morse-codes to the
    computer using your mouse, in case you don't like typing.

@{b}WBDice@{ub} - A dice program, when you can't make up your mind.


@endnode
